cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image synthesis and style transfer. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and feature embeddings further supports this categorization. The paper also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper's focus on balancing content and style, as well as the use of patch-based mechanisms, may also suggest a potential categorization in graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
